#=  Computation Institute, UChicago & Argonne National Laboratory, Chicago, IL.
#+    Grid Consultant (Grid Systems Prod Ops), Globus Alliance, Jan-Sept 2010
#-	 * Automated GridFTP throughput analyses using Bash and LSF scripting   
#--         across the TeraGrid/XSEDE supercomputing centers.
#-	 * Setup custom throughput monitoring (ISIS), refactored GridFTP        
#--         configurations, automated checksumming, and acted as Certificate   
#--         Signing Authority for the Biomedical Informatics Research Network, 
#--         hosted in a custom Nimbus cloud. 
#-	 * Developed scalability testing framework in Bash and Python, and      
#--         implemented service monitoring (Ganglia) for Globus Online GridFTP  
#--         service in the AWS cloud.
printf "\t-o <file>\tSet output file.\n\n" && exit 0; }
#+    Google Summer of Code Student Researcher, Globus Alliance, May-Sept 2009
#-	 * Developed a GridFTP throughput analysis and optimization utility using 
#--         Bash and C++.
# Parse arguments:  
#=  (Self), Oklahoma City, OK. 
#+    Consultant, IT Services, Dec 2006 - Nov 2007
#-	 * Provided outsourced IT services for small to medium-sized businesses
#--         in central Oklahoma.
